==English==

===Etymology===
From the original, superseded genus name {{bor|en|mul|Phylloxera}}, from {{der|en|grc|φύλλον||leaf}} + {{m|grc|ξηρός||dry}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/fɪˈlɒksəɹə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|phylloxerae}}

# An [[insect]], {{taxlink|Daktulosphaira vitifoliae|species|wplink=1}} of the family [[Phylloxeridae]] (not the genus ''[[Phylloxera]]''), that is very destructive to [[grape]] [[vine]]s; also, the diseased condition of a vine caused by this insect. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
#* '''1977''', {{w|Alistair Horne}}, ''A Savage War of Peace'', New York Review Books 2006, p. 32:
#*: thirty-five years later the coming of '''phylloxera''' to France launched the Algerian wine industry, and by the mid-twentieth century it had grown to be one of the Mediterranean's biggest producers.

